<Link id="l00601" /><CodeLine lineNumber="601"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Corresponds to LocalIdAndGlobalIdPair structure.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00602" /><CodeLine lineNumber="602"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// This structure information allows cross-referencing between PDBs.  For</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00603" /><CodeLine lineNumber="603"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// example, when a PDB is being built during compilation it is not yet known</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00604" /><CodeLine lineNumber="604"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// what other modules may end up in the PDB at link time.  So certain types of</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00605" /><CodeLine lineNumber="605"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// IDs may clash between the various compile time PDBs.  For each affected</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
